{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772071182,"nonce":"tsFHIAeb/RavIaAef7hS9mM7uCU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87t_W7P","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/266","origin":"github"},"title":"Evaluate MCP servers for ROS 2 workflows","message":"## Problem\n\nThe workspace could benefit from MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers that expose ROS 2 tooling to AI agents in a structured way. The research identified several existing servers and potential custom integrations.\n\n## Prior work\n\n- [Issue #249 research](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/249), Appendix F: Landscape scan identifying ROSBag MCP Server, ROS 2 Robot Control MCP Server, and custom workspace MCP server concepts\n- MCP is now an industry standard under the Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation\n\n## Scope\n\nThis is exploratory — evaluate, don't commit to building:\n\n1. **ROSBag MCP Server** ([arXiv:2511.03497](https://arxiv.org/abs/2511.03497)) — natural language queries over ROS bag files\n2. **ROS 2 Robot Control MCP Server** — standardized agent access to ROS 2 topics/services\n3. **Custom workspace MCP server** — expose colcon commands, topic inspection, and workspace validation to agents\n\n## Deliverable\n\nA brief evaluation document with recommendation on whether any of these are worth adopting now, or should wait for a concrete use case.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: \\`Claude Code Agent\\`\n**Model**: \\`Claude Opus 4.6\\`","files":null}]}